Kogi State governor, Alhaji Yahaya Bello, has felicitated his Kaduna State counterpart, Governor Nasir el-Rufai on the occasion of his 60th birthday anniversary celebration. Governor Nasir el-Rufai turns 60 on Sunday, 16 February. The congratulatory message was contained in a statement signed by Governor Bello and made available to journalists by his Chief Press Secretary, Onogwu Muhammed, in Lokoja. Governor Bello described Governor el-Rufai as an astounding quantity surveyor, a legal luminary, a quintessential public administrator, a management expert, and a politician per excellence. “I, Alhaji Yahaya Bello, government and good people of Kogi State, heartily congratulate His Excellency, Governor Nasir el-Rufai of Kaduna State on the auspicious occasion of his 60th birthday anniversary. “On this day, I join millions of Nigerians to celebrate an astounding quantity surveyor, a legal luminary, a quintessential public administrator, a management expert cum politician per excellence. ALSO READ: Osun monarch threatens to drag Oluwo to court over alleged assault I was a battery charger, then a typist, before becoming… By de-registering Kowa Party, others, INEC has rewarded… Borno killings: When Northern leaders spoke truth to power Hauwa, the kidnapper who lures her male victims with her… “You have been a rare gift to our generation as your 60 years on earth have made significant contributions to the progress and development of our Father Land. “Your remarkable accomplishments when you served as the Director General of Bureau of Public Enterprises (BPE) as well as the transformation you brought to the nation’s capital, Abuja, when you served as the Minister of FCT still ring the bell whenever the name, ‘Malam el-Rufai’ is mentioned,” Bello said. Bello added that Governor el-Rufai’s first four years as governor of Kaduna State had brought unprecedented progress and development to the people of the state, saying he was confident that his second term would record much more positive accomplishments. Governor Bello further acknowledged and commended the significant supports and contributions made by the celebrant to his reelection for a second term as governor of Kogi State. “As you clock six decades on earth today, I pray that the Almighty Allah will continue to protect and keep you in sound health to enable you to actualise all the good dreams you have for this nation. “Once again, congratulations and happy 60th birthday,” Bello said. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.